    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n771" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀμφι-έπω, ἀμφ-έπω</span></b>  (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἕπω</span>), only part. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀμφιέπων</span> and ipf.: <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">move round, envelop</span>,
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">γάστρην τρίποδος πῦρ ἄμφεπε</span>, <i><span class="en">Il. 18.348</span></i>; of persons, <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">be busy
            about</span>, in preparing meat, attending to sacrifices, etc.,
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ὥς οἵ γ᾽ ἀμφίεπον τάφον Ἕκτορος</span>,
            <i><span class="en">Il. 24.804</span></i>; freq. the part. in
          connection with another verb, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀμφιέποντες</span>, <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">busily.</span>
        </div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
